  "description": [
    "THE HAZARD HERALD THURSDAY DECEMBER 11 1919 THOROUGHBREDS PROVE STRONGER GREAT WAR TAUGHT IMPORT ANCE OF BREEDING OF HORSES RJUJIN6 ENCOURAGED ABROAD Nation Who Bore Brunt of Conflict Maintained the Sport as Much as Passible as Matter of Sound Policy In Its Relation to National Defense At no time In the course of the last fire years not even while the great war was at its height did the Cen tral Empires stop the racing of thor oughbred horses The great tracks at Hamburg Buda Pest Vienna and Ber lin were the scenes of brilliant gather ings etfen when the Grand Duke Nich olas was threatening East Prussia with Invasion and Brurilof was on the edge of the plains of Hungary with his wild Cossack riders At no time dur ing the course of the great war were American and English trainers and Jockeys who had been caught by the declaration of war in Germany and AustriaHungary and were unable to obtain passports interned They were permitted by governments their gov ernments were seeking to destroy tr pursue their accustomed callings un molested and unrestrained To a certain extent racing was cur tailed in Great Britain during the first taro"
